<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Tinvaran</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-30 13:22:51</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I use one of these wpns in my off-hand. I think the fellow<BR>
who said it had a DoT effect may have misinterpreted the <BR>
message "Obsidian shatter effect has worn off" as being due<BR>
to a DoT. I believe this message just indicates when the<BR>
armor-reducing effect has worn off. The proc does 30 DD dmg,<BR>
but I have never observed any other dmg effect when it goes<BR>
off.  When used in conjunction with other proc'ing wpns,<BR>
however (Staff of Writhing[SoW], Yak) it is a nice effect.<BR>
So far the Yak has not proc'ed as much as the SoW...when<BR>
using SoW and this dagger, level 35 or so, and shammy DEX<BR>
buff(total DEX up to 165 with buff), I would frequently see<BR>
4-5 procs from the SOW and this wpn together in a single<BR>
combat, which resulted occasionally in taunting the Mob off<BR>
the tank (ouch!)...you are warned ;-)<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
